  Reads an XML file from https://s3.amazonaws.com/abodo-misc/sample_abodo_feed.xml and extracts the property_id, email, name, and number of bedrooms for that property.

PREREQUISITES
  Install docker, ruby, and dynomodb local
    https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/
    https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/documentation/installation/
    https://hub.docker.com/r/amazon/dynamodb-local/ 

SETUP
  install bundler:
    `gem install bundler`
  install gems
    `bundle install`
  start docker db instance
    `docker run -p 8000:8000 amazon/dynamodb-local`
  setup database
    `ruby db_setup.rb`

Running the parser
  `ruby parse_properties.rb`

Updating weather info
  Install redis 
    wget http://download.redis.io/redis-stable.tar.gz
    tar xvzf redis-stable.tar.gz
    cd redis-stable
    make
    sudo make install
  start redis server
    redis-server
  start sidekiq process
    bundle exec sidekiq -r ./worker.rb
  
  https://www.weather.gov/documentation/services-web-api 
  Example: https://api.weather.gov/gridpoints/TOP/31,80/forecast 
